  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (W-AR-02 adversarial sample)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Higher model risk drives stricter credibility requirements; Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification is performed. This package contains a rebutting defeater: the decision record records Accepted while the Model Form factor achievedLevel (2) remains strictly below requiredLevel (3), a gap that is obscured by extended narrative justification invoking prior experimental campaigns and expert elicitation.",
  "assuranceLevel": "Low",
